        "subtitle": "Synthetic dataset for testing linear regression with noise and outliers",
        "description": "This dataset contains synthetically generated data intended for linear regression modeling. It simulates a linear relationship defined by the equation:\n$$\ny=4.5x+1+noise \n$$\n\n- Number of data points: 230 (200 regular + 30 outliers)\n- Noise: Gaussian noise with standard deviation of 30\n- Outliers: 30 points intentionally added with large deviations to simulate subtle anomalies in the data\n\nThis dataset is ideal for practicing linear regression, outlier detection, and robust modeling techniques.\n\n=== About this file ===\n\nAbout this file\n230 data points, out of which 200 are regular and 30 are outliers\n\n\n=== Columns & descriptions ===\n\nx: The value of x\ny: The value of y\n",
